The Ooni of Ife, Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Ojaja II has lost his grandmother, Madam Comfort Faramobi Ajoke Olasoji Soji-Opa. Mrs. Faramobi gave up the ghost on Saturday night at her residence in Ile-Ife at the ripe age of 103 years. In a statement, signed by Director, Media & Public Affairs, Comrade Moses Olafare, the deceased was Born in 1907 to Chief & Mrs. Aina Akinyemi of the Ajigbayin Compound of Ile-Ife. Survived by children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren, the late Ooni Ogunwusiâ€™s grandmother is scheduled to be buried on Saturday, 13th June 2020 at her residence in Ile-Ife.